    "(iii) The process can be controlled by the input value u(t), while no extra saturations of u are considered for the experimental control design and operation.",
    "(iv) The process input and output are assumed to be available in real-time, while the measured output can naturally be affected by an amplitude-bounded unbiased sensor noise.",
    "Consequently, one can write for the system processG(s) = x(s) u(s) = G(s) 1 s,(1)where the unknown G(s) satisfies the assumption (ii).",
    "Moreover, the overall process G(s) must have a sufficient phase margin, so that closing the loop G(s)[1 + G(s)] -1 would not destabilize the output state.",
    "If it cannot be achieved directly, an additional gaining factor k > 0 can be used to allow for a sufficient phase margin of the open-loop kG(s)."
  ]
